{"PageNumber":8,"Angle":0,"RotatedAngle":0,"Height":1620,"Width":2880,"OriginHeight":0,"OriginWidth":0,"Elements":[{"Index":0,"Type":"title","Text":"#  Key exchange","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":305},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":185},"RightBottom":{"X":928,"Y":305},"RightTop":{"X":928,"Y":185}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":1,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● The use of a symmetric cryptosystem requires that Alice and Bob agree on a secret key before they can send encrypted messages to each other","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":563},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":430},"RightBottom":{"X":2688,"Y":563},"RightTop":{"X":2688,"Y":430}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":2,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Accomplish it by the one-time use of a private communication channel, such as an in-person meeting in a private room, or mailing in tamper-proof containers","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":712},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":584},"RightBottom":{"X":2760,"Y":712},"RightTop":{"X":2760,"Y":584}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":3,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● A key exchange protocol, which is also called key agreement protocol, is a cryptographic approach","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":864},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":733},"RightBottom":{"X":2437,"Y":864},"RightTop":{"X":2437,"Y":733}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":4,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● to establish a shared secret key by communicating solely over an insecure channel, without any previous private communication","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":323,"Y":977},"LeftTop":{"X":323,"Y":867},"RightBottom":{"X":2699,"Y":977},"RightTop":{"X":2699,"Y":867}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":5,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Intuitively, the existence of a key exchange protocol appears unlikely.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":1066},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":998},"RightBottom":{"X":2264,"Y":1066},"RightTop":{"X":2264,"Y":998}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":6,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● as the adversary can arbitrarily disrupt the communication between Alice and Bob","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":323,"Y":1134},"LeftTop":{"X":323,"Y":1073},"RightBottom":{"X":2385,"Y":1134},"RightTop":{"X":2385,"Y":1073}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":7,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Indeed, it can be shown that no key exchange protocol exists if the adversary can actively modify messages sent over the insecure channel","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":1282},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":1156},"RightBottom":{"X":2627,"Y":1282},"RightTop":{"X":2627,"Y":1156}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":8,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Nevertheless, key exchange can be successfully accomplished if the adversary is limited to only passive eavesdropping on messages","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":1437},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":1305},"RightBottom":{"X":2592,"Y":1437},"RightTop":{"X":2592,"Y":1305}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""}]}